{
  "stem": "21308.3",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We were not averse to eating off the land.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "If we came to a German farmer house and there were hausfrau there and we were going to be there for a few minutes, we might tell her to look-- the eggs up and cook them up and we would eat them.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And she would do that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We would eat their eggs.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Unfortunately, some of the troops used to eat the chickens and then complained there were no eggs.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But we got our ration supplies sent up to us.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "The key things a soldier has to have, he has to have his mail from home; he needs food; he needs ammunition; and he needs petrol to get him about.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And of those, food and mail for the individual men is the most important thing.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "You've got to get it to him and it's got to be-- in cold weather, it's got to be hot food.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Well, the British Army was very good at that by 1944.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "We had tins, like tins of baked beans, that they had a candle in them, a self-heating candle, so you could give you a tin of beans, set her up there-- that's your dinner, eat it up.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And the chap would strike across the top on the pad on the candle and then the candle would burn.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And then with the candle finished burning, he'd open up the can and he had a can of hot baked beans.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Pretty good.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, I took my wife on a battlefield tour to or three years after the war finished and we went to the Isle of [INAUDIBLE] and I said, now, that's my slit trench.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "You could still see the slit trench.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
